   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "aa100018",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Section 5: LangChain @tool Implementation\n",
    "\n",
    "### Defining Email Tools with Correct thread_id Handling\n",
    "\n",
    "LangChain tools are Python functions decorated with `@tool`. The function's docstring becomes the tool description that the LLM reads — write it carefully, because the LLM uses it to decide when and how to call the tool.\n",
    "\n",
    "The key design principle: the tool itself manages thread_id persistence. The LLM does not know about thread_ids — it just asks to \"send a reply\" and the tool infrastructure handles the state.\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Production note:** Avoid putting thread_id in the tool's parameters that the LLM fills in. LLMs will hallucinate thread_ids — they might plausibly guess `th_abc123` for a different conversation. Thread_ids should come only from your storage layer or directly from webhook payloads."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "aa100019",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from langchain_core.tools import tool\n",
    "from commune import CommuneClient\n",
    "from typing import Optional\n",
    "\n",
    "# These are closed over by the tool functions below\n",
    "_client = CommuneClient(api_key=COMMUNE_API_KEY)\n",
    "_thread_store = InMemoryThreadStore()  # swap for RedisThreadStore in production\n",
    "_inbox_id = \"inb_your_inbox_id\"  # replace with your actual inbox ID\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "@tool\n",
    "def send_initial_email(to: str, subject: str, body: str) -> str:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Send an opening email to a new contact. Use this ONLY for the first email\n",
    "    to a recipient — it starts a new conversation thread.\n",
    "    For replies to existing conversations, use reply_to_contact instead.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Args:\n",
    "        to: Recipient email address\n",
    "        subject: Email subject line (keep concise, under 60 chars)\n",
    "        body: Email body in plain text\n",
    "\n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        Confirmation string with message status\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    result = _client.messages.send(\n",
    "        from_inbox_id=_inbox_id,\n",
    "        to=to,\n",
    "        subject=subject,\n",
    "        text=body,\n",
    "        # No thread_id — this is intentionally a new thread\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Persist thread_id immediately\n",
    "    _thread_store.set(\n",
    "        key=f\"contact:{to}\",\n",
    "        thread_id=result.thread_id,\n",
    "        ttl_seconds=90 * 24 * 3600,  # 90 days\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    return f\"Email sent to {to}. Thread ID: {result.thread_id}. Status: sent.\"\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "@tool\n",
    "def reply_to_contact(to: str, body: str) -> str:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Reply to an existing email conversation with a contact.\n",
    "    Automatically continues the conversation thread — the reply will appear\n",
    "    grouped with previous messages in the recipient's email client.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Use this for ALL replies after the first email has been sent.\n",
    "    Do NOT use send_initial_email for replies — it will start a new thread.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Args:\n",
    "        to: Recipient email address (must have an existing conversation)\n",
    "        body: Reply body in plain text\n",
    "\n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        Confirmation string, or error if no existing thread found\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    thread_id = _thread_store.get(key=f\"contact:{to}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    if thread_id is None:\n",
    "        return (\n",
    "            f\"No existing conversation thread found for {to}. \"\n",
    "            f\"Use send_initial_email to start a new conversation.\"\n",
    "        )\n",
    "\n",
    "    result = _client.messages.send(\n",
    "        from_inbox_id=_inbox_id,\n",
    "        thread_id=thread_id,\n",
    "        text=body,\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    return f\"Reply sent to {to} in thread {thread_id}. Status: sent.\"\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "@tool\n",
    "def get_thread_history(to: str, limit: int = 10) -> str:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Retrieve the recent message history for a conversation with a contact.\n",
    "    Use this to get context before drafting a reply — understanding the\n",
    "    full conversation history leads to more relevant and coherent responses.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Args:\n",
    "        to: Contact's email address\n",
    "        limit: Maximum number of messages to retrieve (default: 10, max: 50)\n",
    "\n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "        Formatted conversation history as a string\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    thread_id = _thread_store.get(key=f\"contact:{to}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    if thread_id is None:\n",
    "        return f\"No existing conversation with {to}.\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    messages = _client.messages.list(\n",
    "        thread_id=thread_id,\n",
    "        limit=min(limit, 50),\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    if not messages:\n",
    "        return f\"No messages found in thread {thread_id}.\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    history_parts = []\n",
    "    for msg in reversed(messages):  # oldest first\n",
    "        direction = \"Sent\" if msg.direction == \"outbound\" else \"Received\"\n",
    "        history_parts.append(\n",
    "            f\"[{msg.created_at.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M')}] {direction}:\\n{msg.text or msg.html}\\n\"\n",
    "        )\n",
    "\n",
    "    return \"\\n---\\n\".join(history_parts)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"LangChain tools defined: send_initial_email, reply_to_contact, get_thread_history\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print(\"Key design choice: thread_id is managed by the tool, not exposed to the LLM.\")\n",
    "print(\"The LLM only needs to know: 'send to this person' — not the thread_id.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "aa100020",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Complete LangChain Agent with Persistent Thread State\n",
    "\n",
    "Now we assemble the full agent: LangChain `ChatOpenAI` model, the email tools, and LangChain's `ConversationBufferMemory` to carry agent context across turns.\n",
    "\n",
    "Note the two types of memory at play here:\n",
    "1. **LangChain memory** (`ConversationBufferMemory`) — the agent's own reasoning history across API calls. This is ephemeral in-process state.\n",
    "2. **Thread store** (`InMemoryThreadStore` or `RedisThreadStore`) — the email thread_id persistence. This is durable cross-process state.\n",
    "\n",
    "Both are necessary. Neither replaces the other."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "aa100021",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from langchain_openai import ChatOpenAI\n",
    "from langchain.agents import create_tool_calling_agent, AgentExecutor\n",
    "from langchain.memory import ConversationBufferMemory\n",
    "from langchain_core.prompts import ChatPromptTemplate, MessagesPlaceholder\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define the agent's tools\n",
    "tools = [send_initial_email, reply_to_contact, get_thread_history]\n",
    "\n",
    "# System prompt that teaches the agent about thread continuity\n",
    "system_prompt = \"\"\"\n",
    "You are a customer support agent with access to email tools.\n",
    "\n",
    "Email threading rules you must follow:\n",
    "1. For the FIRST email to a contact: use send_initial_email\n",
    "2. For ALL replies: use reply_to_contact (this preserves thread continuity)\n",
    "3. Before drafting a reply: use get_thread_history to understand context\n",
    "4. Never use send_initial_email as a reply — it breaks the email thread\n",
    "\n",
    "When replying, always read the thread history first so your response is contextually accurate.\n",
    "Keep replies concise and helpful. Acknowledge specific points raised in the customer's message.\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "prompt = ChatPromptTemplate.from_messages([\n",
    "    (\"system\", system_prompt),\n",
    "    MessagesPlaceholder(variable_name=\"chat_history\"),\n",
    "    (\"human\", \"{input}\"),\n",
    "    MessagesPlaceholder(variable_name=\"agent_scratchpad\"),\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "llm = ChatOpenAI(model=\"gpt-4o\", api_key=OPENAI_API_KEY, temperature=0.2)\n",
    "\n",
    "agent = create_tool_calling_agent(llm=llm, tools=tools, prompt=prompt)\n",
    "\n",
    "memory = ConversationBufferMemory(\n",
    "    memory_key=\"chat_history\",\n",
    "    return_messages=True,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "agent_executor = AgentExecutor(\n",
    "    agent=agent,\n",
    "    tools=tools,\n",
    "    memory=memory,\n",
    "    verbose=True,  # set False in production to reduce log noise\n",
    "    handle_parsing_errors=True,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"LangChain agent initialized with email tools and conversation memory.\")"
   ]
  },
