    "## Section 6: Multi-Agent Thread Isolation\n",
    "\n",
    "### What Happens When Multiple Agents Share an Inbox\n",
    "\n",
    "The thread_id collision problem is worst in multi-agent setups where multiple LangChain chains share one inbox. Here is the exact failure scenario:\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Production note:** This is not hypothetical. If you ever see customers receive replies from the wrong agent (e.g., a billing inquiry getting a technical support response), inbox sharing is almost always the cause."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "aa100025",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Illustrating the thread_id collision in a shared inbox scenario\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Thread collision scenario — shared inbox\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 60)\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print(\"Shared inbox: support@yourdomain.commune.email\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print(\"Timeline:\")\n",
    "print(\"  T+0:  Customer A emails about BILLING → thread th_aaa\")\n",
    "print(\"        billing_agent handles it, stores: contact:customerA@→th_aaa\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print(\"  T+5:  Customer A replies to billing thread\")\n",
    "print(\"        Webhook fires with thread_id=th_aaa\")\n",
    "print(\"        billing_agent looks up contact:customerA@... → th_aaa ✅\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print(\"  T+10: Customer B emails about TECHNICAL issue → thread th_bbb\")\n",
    "print(\"        tech_agent handles it\")\n",
    "print(\"        BOTH agents share the same _thread_store and inbox_id\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print(\"  T+15: Customer A replies again\")\n",
    "print(\"        Webhook fires with thread_id=th_aaa to SHARED inbox\")\n",
    "print(\"        Both agents receive the event\")\n",
    "print(\"        tech_agent picks it up (race condition)\")\n",
    "print(\"        tech_agent has no thread for customerA → treats as new\")\n",
    "print(\"        OR: tech_agent overwrites billing thread_id in shared store\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print(\"Result: Customer A gets a technical support reply to their billing question.\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print(\"─\" * 60)\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print(\"Per-inbox solution — no collision possible:\")\n",
    "print(\"  billing@yourdomain.commune.email   → webhook always goes to billing_agent\")\n",
    "print(\"  support@yourdomain.commune.email   → webhook always goes to tech_agent\")\n",
    "print(\"  Route by inbox_id in webhook payload — O(1), zero ambiguity\")"
   ]
